According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Food-Grade Phosphate Market was valued at USD 2.48 billion in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 2.63 billion in 2025 to USD 3.76 billion by 2032, registering a CAGR of 6.3% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing steady expansion due to the increasing consumption of processed and convenience foods, rising demand for high-quality meat and dairy products, and the essential role of food-grade phosphates in improving texture, moisture retention, shelf life, and product stability. Ongoing innovations in specialty phosphate formulations and clean-label compatible solutions are further supporting market growth across global food processing industries.
